## Architecture audit checklist and hardening fixes

### End-to-end pipeline flow

A hardened ingestion loop should look like this:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Scheduler trigger] --> B[Acquire ingest lock]
  B --> C[Compute poll window: since/until with overlap]
  C --> D[Build request: params + headers + auth]
  D --> E[Fetch page 1]
  E --> F{More pages?}
  F -- yes --> G[Fetch next page]
  G --> F
  F -- no --> H[Parse raw items]
  H --> I[Normalize + validate fields]
  I --> J[Compute dedupe key / natural key]
  J --> K[UPSERT crash_reports]
  K --> L[Lead creation rule]
  L --> M[Mark processed_to_lead + link lead_id]
  M --> N[Write ingest_run summary + metrics]
  N --> O[Release lock]
```

Key production implication: retries and pagination happen **before** parsing and database writes; idempotency and dedupe happen **before** lead creation; and every run writes a summarized ŌĆ£what happenedŌĆØ record that the admin UI can show.

