### UPSERT patterns for idempotent ingestion

UPSERT is purpose-built for ŌĆ£insert or update if exists,ŌĆØ which is exactly what resilient ingestion needs. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn15search1Ņłü

```sql
INSERT INTO crash_reports (
  source, source_report_id, occurred_at, reported_at,
  raw_payload, raw_payload_sha256, ingest_trace_id,
  last_seen_at
) VALUES (
  $1, $2, $3, $4,
  $5::jsonb, $6, $7,
  NOW()
)
ON CONFLICT (source, source_report_id)
DO UPDATE SET
  reported_at = EXCLUDED.reported_at,
  raw_payload = EXCLUDED.raw_payload,
  raw_payload_sha256 = EXCLUDED.raw_payload_sha256,
  ingest_trace_id = EXCLUDED.ingest_trace_id,
  last_seen_at = NOW();
```

This gives you three critical properties:

1. You can re-run any window safely.
2. Overlap windows donŌĆÖt flood your DB.
3. You can update a record if FLHSMV later enriches/fixes it.

